        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Israel and Lebanon are expected to hold direct talks in the coming days Middle East Issued on: 14/03/2026 - 17:54 An overnight Israeli strike in southern Lebanon killed a dozen health workers at a clinic, with health authorities saying 26 paramedics have been killed since March 2. Israel and Lebanon ​are expected to hold direct talks in the coming days, their first since the start of ​the ‌Iran war that has ⁠drawn Lebanon deeper into conflict, Israeli newspaper Haaretz reported on ‌Saturday. Details by FRANCE 24 correspondent in Jerusalem, Noga Tarnopolsky. Israel threatens to strike ambulances in Lebanon in Hezbollah fighting 14/03/2026 Middle East Why did the US military bomb the strategic Iranian island of Kharg? 14/03/2026 Middle East Why did the US bomb Kharg Island? What is its significance for Iran? 14/03/2026 Middle East Israeli strike kills 12 medics in a clinic in southern Lebanon 14/03/2026 Middle East 14/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon says 26 paramedics were killed in Israeli strikes since March 2 14/03/2026 Middle East Iran threatens United Arab Emirate's ports and docks 14/03/2026 Middle East NATO defence systems shoot down Iranian ballistic missile over Turkey 14/03/2026 Middle East Two weeks into the war in the Middle East - What happens next? 14/03/2026 Analysis Middle East"
